    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine Domini Dei Salvatoris nostri Iesu Christi. Firmavimus atque
                        concessimus nos domnus <rs key="#Vir_gloriosus/vir_sublimis">vir
                            gloriosissimus</rs>
                        <persName ref="#people/2004" key="#Marquis/duke">Romuvvald</persName> summus
                            <rs key="#Marquis/duke">dux</rs> genti Langobardorum in <orgName
                            key="#Churches #Private_foundations" ref="#juridical_persons/3401"><rs
                                key="#Churches #Private_foundations">ęcclesia</rs> Beate
                            Sophie</orgName> quam <persName ref="#people/3453" key="#Abbots"
                            >Zacharia</persName> venerabilis <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs> noster a
                        fundamentis edificare visus est in locum qui nominatur <placeName
                            ref="#places/3426"
                            key="#Villages/settlements #Houses #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Landed_possessions #Mills #Fruits/vegetables #Animals #Cows #Horses #Sheep #Fiscal_property"
                            >ad Ponticello</placeName>, quod fuit de quodam <name ref="Wadulfus"
                            >Vvadulfi</name>, omnia et in omnibus de quod nostra potesta predicti
                        Zacharię abbati concessimus, unde et nostra habet <rs
                            key="#Marquis’/ducal/princely_diploma">firmata preceptora</rs>, id est
                        in primis <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><rs key="#Houses">casas</rs> cum <rs key="#Curtes">cortes</rs> vel
                                <rs key="#Fruits/vegetables #Agricultural_workers">hortoras</rs>,
                                <rs key="#Mills">molino</rs> et balneo, <rs>clausurias</rs></rs> ubi
                        ipsa ęcclesia edificata est, et <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >terra</rs> bacua qui est trans rivo, et alio <rs
                            key="#Fruits/vegetables">horto</rs> qui esset videtur iuxta fluvium
                            <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/2348">Sabbato</placeName>, qui
                        fuit de quodam <name ref="Trasualdus">Trasoaldi</name>, <rs key="#Casalia"
                            >casale</rs> in <placeName ref="#places/2304"
                            key="#Villages/settlements #Casalia #Fiscal_property"
                            >Quintodecimo</placeName> qui fuit de quodam <name ref="Pergoaldus"
                            >Pergoaldi</name>, <rs key="#Fiscal_property"><rs key="#Houses"
                                >casas</rs>, <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terras</rs>, <rs
                                key="#Wine">vineas</rs>, pratas et <rs>clausurias</rs>, cultum vel
                            incultum, omnia et in omnibus in quantum in eodem locum habere visus
                            fuit</rs>, simul et omnem substantiam quam <name ref="Toto Transpadanus"
                            >Totoni Transpadano</name>, <rs key="#Fiscal_property"><rs key="#Houses"
                                >casas</rs>, <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terras</rs>, <rs
                                key="#Wine">vineas</rs>, cultum vel incultum, movilia atque
                            inmovilia</rs>, qui habitare visus fuit erga <placeName
                            ref="#places/3420" key="#Villages/settlements #Fiscal_property">Sancto
                            Balentino</placeName>, <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >territurio</rs> in locum qui dicitur Salito <rs key="#Fines">de</rs>
                        rivo qui descendit de Monte Benedicti et usque <placeName ref="#places/2323"
                            key="#Rivers #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property">fluvium
                            Sangro</placeName> et de alio latere a rivo Sonolo qui mergit de
                        Castello Urso et usque in nostro fluvio Sangro et desuper fini habet una in
                        capo de ripa et usquem in ipsum fluvium Sangro, et omnem substantiam qui
                        fuit <name ref="Aloaldus"/>Aloaldi filio quoddam <name ref="Sassulus"
                            >Sasoli</name>, <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >tam <rs key="#Houses">casas</rs> infra <rs
                                key="#Cities #Fiscal_property">Beneventana</rs> civitatem quam <rs
                                key="#Casalia">casalis</rs> et <rs key="#Domuscultae">domui
                                cultas</rs>, <rs key="#Wine">vineas</rs>, <rs
                                key="#Landed_possessions">terras</rs>, cultum vel incultum, movilia
                            atque inmovilia</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >territurio</rs> in locus qui nominatur <placeName ref="#places/2844"
                            key="#Rivers #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property">Fluvium
                            Lauri</placeName>, quas cum <name ref="Paulus abbas">Paulo</name> et
                            <name ref="Deusdedit abbas">Deusdedi</name> venerabilis <rs
                            key="#Abbots">abbatis</rs> habere visus fuisti, et substantia qui fuit
                        quodam <name ref="Iulianus">Iuliani</name>, omnia et in omnibus in quantum
                        eius portio fuit, quas cum Deusdedi abbate habere visus fuisti, <rs
                            key="#Sheep #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Specialized_workers"
                            >pecoras cum mandras et pastoris suos</rs> qui fuerunt de <name
                            ref="Iohannes">Iohannis</name> et alias <rs
                            key="#Sheep #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Specialized_workers"
                            >pecoras cum mandras et pastoris suos</rs> qui fuerunt de <name
                            ref="Vigilus">Vigili</name>, <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><rs key="#Horses">ammessario uno cum iomentas suas, caballos
                                domitos capitas quindecim</rs>, <rs key="#Cows">armentum de baccas
                                et bobes domitos</rs>, <rs>carras ferratas</rs>, <rs key="#Silver"
                                >argentum</rs>, <rs key="#Copper">heramentum</rs></rs> ad omnia
                        quicquid ipse abbas Zacharias sua expontanea voluntatem in ipsum veneravilis
                        locum Beate Sophię offerri voluerit, in ea vero rationem de hec omnia in
                        beneravilis ecclesia Sancte Sophię nostrum preceptum firmavimus, eo quod <rs
                            key="#Public_exactions #Privileges #Exemption">ab omnis subiugationis
                            hominibus ea absolvimus</rs> ut nęque ab episcopum dominetur, nęque ad
                        monasteria subiugata, neque a sinodochio defendatur, sed <rs key="#Priests"
                            >sacerdos</rs> qui in eodem monasterium deservierit absoluta securitas
                        ei permaneat, <rs key="#Immunity">exceptum ad nostrum sacrum palatium
                            obedientia habeat</rs>; et si quis contra hunc preceptum firmationis
                        atque offertionis temtare voluerit, habeat portionem cum Iudas traditore
                        Domini nostri Iesu Christi, quatenus ab hodierna die sit nostre preceptum
                        firmum et stabilito et ab omnis subiugationem absolutus et in perpetuis
                        temporibus firmum et inviolatus permaneat. Quod vero preceptum firmationis
                        atque offertionis ex iussione nostre potestati dictavi ego <persName
                            key="#Other_palatine_officer" ref="#people/3454">Persus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_palatine_officer">vicedominus et referendario</rs> tibi
                            <persName key="#Notary" ref="#people/3480">Theodoald</persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> scribendum. Acto <placeName key="#Cities"
                            ref="#places/110">Benevento</placeName> in palatio mense martio per
                        indictione septima. Feliciter.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
